## Conclusion

This lab demonstrated the initial reconnaissance phase of an attack by performing host discovery with Nmap. While the activity was successfully observed from the attacker’s perspective, no corresponding Wazuh alerts were generated because default endpoint monitoring does not typically detect ICMP-based host discovery. This highlights the importance of combining endpoint telemetry with network monitoring to improve visibility into reconnaissance activities.
